{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nGates must each read their own kind, reopen must invalidate without mutating records, and\nthe retire_attested_pin blank-SIGNATURE mutation conflicts with the immutable-record model.\n## What\nAdd `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind)` in the verification layer\ncentralizing per-kind rules; the MATERIAL-CHANGE field set is a named constant\n(description/AC/file_impact/children). Point `claim_gate_check` at `kind=\"plan-review\"` and\nthe close gate + completion child-closure check (`completion.py`, currently\n`verify_signature(cid).get(\"verdict\")`) at `kind=\"completion-verifier\"`. REMOVE\n`retire_attested_pin` (signing.py:406-440) and its reopen call (transition.py:503-506);\nboth kinds become reopen-aware via validity-on-read (\"not reopened since signed_at\").\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (`claim_gate_check`, `compute_validity`),\n`src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` (close gate; remove retire_attested_pin call),\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (remove retire_attested_pin), `src/rebar/llm/completion.py`.\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind)` centralizes per-kind validity; MATERIAL-CHANGE set is a named constant.\n- [ ] Claim gate verifies `plan-review`; close + child-closure verify `completion-verifier`.\n- [ ] completion valid = certified AND closed AND not-reopened-since AND material-unchanged-since signed_at.\n- [ ] plan-review valid = existing freshness AND not-reopened-since signed_at.\n- [ ] `retire_attested_pin` removed; no lifecycle transition mutates any attestation record."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782783724025953001,"uuid":"7fb7fd75-7d3e-4d83-aeeb-785fcf3889ac"}